<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-28T10:49:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-28T10:49:00-05:00" n="540" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d540">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1221.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-28T11:00:00-04:49">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 28, 1915—11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>At 10.30 mob invaded French Legation, took out President, killed and
                            dismembered him before Legation gates. Hysterical crowds parading
                            streets with portions of his body on poles.</p>
                        <p>U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi> entering harbor.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>